Assert.AreEqual(247.50m, order.TotalAmount);
Assert.AreEqual(22.28m, order.TaxAmount);
Assert.AreEqual(269.78m, order.GrandTotal);
```

**Fix:** Derive expected values from named constants or document the calculation:

```csharp
// ✅ Fixed — self-documenting expectations
const decimal sku1Price = 59.99m;
const decimal sku2Price = 67.53m;
const decimal expectedSubtotal = (sku1Price * 3) + (sku2Price * 1); // 247.50
const decimal taxRate = 0.09m;
const decimal expectedTax = Math.Round(expectedSubtotal * taxRate, 2);  // 22.28
const decimal expectedTotal = expectedSubtotal + expectedTax;           // 269.78

Assert.AreEqual(expectedSubtotal, order.TotalAmount);
Assert.AreEqual(expectedTax, order.TaxAmount);
Assert.AreEqual(expectedTotal, order.GrandTotal);
```

**Risk if unfixed:** If prices or tax rates change, no one will know whether the new values are correct or a bug.

